ğŸ­ Controlled Breathing Techniques
Analysis (serious tone): Breathing is not just survivalâ€”it can be trained, shaped, and 
refined. Here are some classic methods:

Diaphragmatic / Belly breathing: inhale deep into the abdomen, not just the chest.

Box breathing (4-4-4-4): inhale, hold, exhale, holdâ€”each for 4 seconds.

4-7-8 breathing: inhale for 4, hold for 7, exhale for 8; deeply relaxing.

Pursed-lip breathing: exhale slowly through tightened lips to prolong the breath.

Equal breathing (sama vritti): inhale and exhale for the same duration.

Resonant breathing (coherent breathing): breathe at a steady rhythm of 5â€“6 cycles per 
minute.

Alternate nostril breathing (nadi shodhana): inhale through one nostril, exhale through 
the other.

Lionâ€™s breath: exhale with mouth wide open and tongue out, like a roaring lion.

Sitali breath: inhale through a rolled tongue, cooling the body.

Humming bee breath (bhramari): exhale with a buzzing sound, like a bee.

ğŸ‘‰ Any of these techniques can be learned and adapted. If you want to explore them, ask 
Copilot to turn them into practical exercises.

